20 references to retailers from certain provisions governing requirements for entities
21 who sell dogs or cats. Section 9 of this bill provides that the provisions of section 2
22 do not apply to certain activities.
23 Existing law provides, with certain exceptions, that a person who sells or
24 attempts to sell, offers for adoption or transfers ownership of a live animal at a
25 swap meet is guilty of a misdemeanor. Existing law, as an exception to such a
26 prohibition, authorizes a person to perform such acts at a swap meet if it is
27 conducted in a county or incorporated city in this State that has authorized, by an
28 ordinance which meets certain requirements, such a sale and the person performs
29 such acts in accordance with the ordinance. (NRS 574.550) Section 18 of this bill
30 instead prohibits a person from selling, attempting to sell or offering for adoption or
31 transferring ownership of a dog or cat at a swap meet, without exception.
