1 Section 1. Chapter 574 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. A retail pet store shall not sell, offer to sell,
4 barter, auction or otherwise transfer ownership of any dog or cat.
5 2. Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit a
6 retail pet store from collaborating with an animal shelter or
7 animal rescue organization for the purpose of adoption to provide
8 space to showcase dogs or cats under the care of the animal
9 shelter or animal rescue organization. A retail pet store that
10 provides space to an animal shelter or animal rescue organization
11 in such a manner must not receive any compensation for
12 showcasing the dog or cat or any portion of the fees that result
13 from the adoption of the dog or cat.
14 3. An operator of a retail pet store that violates the provisions
15 of this section is guilty of a misdemeanor.
16 4. For the purposes of prosecuting a violation of this section,
17 each act that constitutes a violation of this section is a separate
18 offense. In addition to any other penalty that may be imposed, the
19 court may prohibit a person who is guilty of a misdemeanor
20 pursuant to subsection 3 from selling any dogs or cats that he or
21 she is otherwise authorized to sell as a breeder or dealer, if
22 applicable, pursuant to the provisions of this chapter for not more
23 than 1 year.
24 5. As used in this section, “animal rescue organization” has
25 the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.205. The term does not
26 include a dealer, a breeder or any organization that is located on
27 the premises of or shares employees with a breeder.
